analysisPopulations.name: Randomized subjects
analysisPopulations.text: Subjects who are randomized via the Interactive Web Response System (IWRS). For efficacy analyses and baseline summaries, subjects will be analyzed according to their randomization assignment.
analysisPopulations.label: ITT
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Subjects who are randomized via the Interactive Web Response System (IWRS). For efficacy analyses and baseline summaries, subjects will be analyzed according to their randomization assignment.

analysisPopulations.name: Treated subjects
analysisPopulations.text: Randomized subjects who receive at least one dose of double-blind study medication. For safety analysis (eg, adverse events [AEs]) and summary of exposure, subjects will be analyzed according to the predominant treatment received (defined as the treatment to which the subject was exposed for the greatest duration).
analysisPopulations.label: On-Study / On-Treatment
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Randomized subjects who receive at least one dose of double-blind study medication. For safety analysis (eg, adverse events [AEs]) and summary of exposure, subjects will be analyzed according to the predominant treatment received (defined as the treatment to which the subject was exposed for the greatest duration).
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 dose of double-blind study medication

characteristics.name: eGFR
characteristics.description: Estimated glomerular filtration rate used for stratification (>=30 to <45, >=45 to <60, >=60 to <90 mL/min/1.73m2)

characteristics.name: UACR
characteristics.description: Urinary albumin-to-creatinine ratio (level >300 mg/g to <=5,000 mg/g for eligibility)

characteristics.name: Serum Creatinine
characteristics.description: Baseline average derived from the Day 1 value and the value immediately preceding the Day 1 determination
